-- Eskom Says 8,395 Megawatts of Capacity Out
-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 2012-05-07T15:00:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-07/eskom-says-8-395-megawatts-of-capacity-out-correct-.html
(Corrects figure in headline.)  Eskom Holdings SOC Ltd.,  South
Africa ’s state-owned power utility, said today equipment with
the capacity to generate 3,415 megawatts is undergoing planned
maintenance.  A further 4,980 megawatts isn’t available because of
unplanned outages, the Johannesburg-based company said in an e-
mailed statement. Eskom’s capacity to meet peak demand today is
34,559 megawatts while demand is forecast at 32,906  megawatts,
it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
